meta {
  name: Bulk Import Lab Tests
  type: http
  seq: 10
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/master-data/{{masterDataId}}/lab-tests/import
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "rows": [
      {
        "rowNumber": 2,
        "testName": "Vitamin D (25-OH)",
        "testCode": "VITD",
        "samplePriorityType": "ROUTINE",
        "priceMsrp": 1200,
        "priceMaximum": 1100,
        "priceMinimum": 900,
        "commissionPrice": 80,
        "tatMaxValue": 48,
        "tatMaxUnit": "HOURS"
      },
      {
        "rowNumber": 3,
        "testName": "Thyroid Profile (T3 T4 TSH)",
        "testCode": "THYROID",
        "priceMsrp": 800
      }
    ]
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  masterDataId: 3bebbd8d-eef4-4bfa-88f3-3aff4a4a4516
}

tests {
  test("201 Created", function () {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(201);
  });
  test("reports created count", function () {
    const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
    expect(data).to.have.property("created");
  });
}

docs {
  Bulk-import lab tests (**create-only**) from the frontend's parsed Excel rows.
  `rows` is an array (1–1000) of **core/scalar** test fields — no nested
  samples/parameters. Each row may carry an optional `rowNumber` (echoed in error
  messages; falls back to the 1-based index). `testName` and `testCode` are
  required per row.
  
  ## Behaviour
  
  - **Validate-all-then-save (all-or-nothing).** Every row is validated first —
    structural (types/required/enum), cross-field invariants (price ordering,
    mandatory-dept, repeat-interval), and **duplicate** `testName`/`testCode`
    (both within the batch and against existing active tests in the master data).
  - If **any** row fails → 422 `LAB_TEST_IMPORT_VALIDATION_FAILED` whose `message`
    is a row-numbered list, and **nothing** is saved. See "Bulk Import Lab Tests -
    Validation Errors".
  - On success every row is created in one transaction (seeded `versionHistory`
    v1) → `{ created: <count> }`.
  - This API does **not** update existing tests — a row matching an existing
    `testName`/`testCode` is reported as a duplicate error.
}
